author: Staff Reports
title: Valwood volleyball goes undefeated
text:
Valwood volleyball goes undefeated Staff Reports Valdosta Daily Times 
The Valwood volleyball team put the finishing touches on an undefeated season Wednesday afternoon as it defeated Tift County High School 3-1 (25-10, 22-25, 25-12, 26-24) at the Eager Sports Center. 
The Valiants (17-0) opened the day by celebrating the three seniors on the team — Brenna Wilson, Dominique Denny and Emily Johnson — then looked like they would coast to an easy victory with a 25-10 opening-set win. 
But the Blue Devils bounced back to take the second game by three points. But the Valiants responded by dominating Game 3 and then had to go extra points to close out their final victory of the regular season. 
The Valiants were led by their continuous standouts from all season as Erin Moss had 12 kills and two aces, Maylee McLeod had 11 digs and three aces, Ashley Manwell had five digs, three kills, 31 assists and four aces, and Johnson added nine kills. 
Valwood will next prepare for the GISA state playoffs, which will begin on Friday, Oct. 23. The Valiants will be a No. 1 seed.
